#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:4
msgid ""
"TITLE:\t\tGRUB Boot & Rescue Disk - HOWTO LFS Version:\tAll "
"AUTHOR:\t\tDaniel Armstrong <daniel_armstrong@sympatico.ca>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:10
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"SYNOPSIS:\n"
"\tGRUB is the GRand Unified Bootloader, a boot loader program with many\n"
"cool features for the PC. It serves as a replacement for the more "
"traditional\n"
"LILO. This hint shows how to use GRUB to make a combined boot loader and "
"rescue \n"
"disk for your LFS system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:15
msgid ""
"HINT: If you do not currently have GRUB installed on your system, you will "
"need to download the most recent version "
"(ftp://alpha.gnu.org/gnu/grub/grub-0.90.tar.gz)  and install it into your "
"chosen working directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:17
msgid "Now we unpack GRUB and install it on our system with the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:23
msgid ""
"tar xvzf grub-0.90.tar.gz cd grub-0.90 ./configure --prefix=/usr make make "
"install"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:26
msgid ""
"This will create the necessary executables and support files to create our "
"boot and rescue disk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:28
msgid "Grab a spare floppy and do a fresh format and install a filesystem:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:31
msgid "fdformat /dev/fd0 mkfs -t ext2 /dev/fd0"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:33
msgid "Now we need to mount our soon-to-be GRUB disk:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:35
msgid "mount -t ext2 /dev/fd0 /mnt"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:38
msgid ""
"Create the directory and install the files GRUB will need to serve as your "
"boot loader:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:42
msgid ""
"mkdir -p /mnt/boot/grub cp /usr/share/grub/i386-pc/stage1 /mnt/boot/grub cp "
"/usr/share/grub/i386-pc/stage2 /mnt/boot/grub"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:47
msgid ""
"Now we are going to setup our GRUB floppy to do double-duty as a rescue disk "
"for our LFS system, by placing a copy of the kernel on our floppy. This way "
"if kernel on the hard drive is ever corrupted or trashed, we can use our "
"GRUB boot and rescue disk to get our system up and running again."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:49
msgid "Copy your kernel to the GRUB floppy:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:51
msgid "cp /boot/vmlinuz-2.4.7 /mnt/boot\t#Your kernel and location may vary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:55
msgid ""
"The final step before we reboot and test our GRUB boot and rescue disk is to "
"install the GRUB tools in the Master Boot Record (MBR) of the "
"floppy. Unmount the floppy but leave it in the drive:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:57
msgid "umount /dev/fd0"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:59
msgid "Now type at the command prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:61
msgid "grub"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:64
msgid ""
"This starts up the GRUB shell environment and changes your # prompt to "
"\"grub>\".  Now enter:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:68
msgid "root (fd0)  setup (fd0)  quit"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:71
msgid ""
"Your GRUB boot and rescue disk is now complete. Leave the floppy in the "
"drive and reboot. When the GRUB shell returns type:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:76
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"root (fd0)\n"
"kernel /boot/vmlinuz-2.4.7 root=/dev/hda3\t#Replace MY boot image and root\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t\t#partition with your own\n"
"boot\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:78
msgid "Voila! Your LFS system should be up and running now."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/grub_boot_rescue.txt:82
msgid ""
"For a more complete description of GRUB's many features, configuration, and "
"installing GRUB on your hard drive's MBR, see the \"Grub-HOWTO\" hint at the "
"LFS-Hints website and/or type \"info grub\" at your command prompt."
msgstr ""

